land":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Brien","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Brigid, Declan, Donovan, John Patrick, Kieran, Colm, Donal, Brennan, Caitlin.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Briain</b> ‘descendant of <i>Brian</i>’, a personal name probably based on the element <i>bre-</i> ‘hill’, with the transferred sense ‘eminence’, i.e. ‘exalted one’. See also   Bryan  . In Ireland there has also been some confusion with   O'Byrne   (see   Byrne  ).","History: This name is borne in particular by one of the greatest of Irish septs, descendants of Brian Boru, who rose to the high kingship of Ireland in 1002."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Brion","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish William Kevin.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"Bryan","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Briant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  , with excrescent <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"O'Bryant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"McBrien","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Seamus.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Briain</b> ‘son of Brian’. See   O'Brien   and   Bryan  ."]},{"name":"O'Brian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Padraic.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]}]},{"name":"Slany","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which has recently come to be used fairly regularly in the United States as a given name for boys and less frequently also for girls."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Slany O'Brien was born in 1285, in Thomond, County Clare, Ireland, her father, Conor Conchobar OBrien, was 21 and her mother, Sabina O'Kennedy, was 18. She had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Sir Nicholas fitzMaurice fitzThomas 3rd Baron of Kerry and Lixnaw. She died on 20 April 1344, in Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1285–20 Apr 1344":"1285–20. aprill 1344","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1280–1317":"1280–1317","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1308–1378":"1308–1378","1318–1358":"1318–1358","–1339":"–1339","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","19 Jul 1329":"19. juuli 1329","20 Apr 1344":"20. aprill 1344","1285":"1285","1280":"1280","1358":"1358","1215":"1215","1303":"1303","1378":"1378","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1308":"1308","1318":"1318","1329":"1329","1317":"1317","1339":"1339","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Iirimaa","County Kerry, Ireland":"County Kerry, Iirimaa","Battle of Thurles (Slain)":"Battle, Camrose County No. 22, Alberta, Kanada","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Ardfert, County Kerry, Ireland":"Ardfert, County Kerry, Iirimaa","Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1285–20 Apr 1344":"1285–20. huhtikuuta 1344","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1280–1317":"1280–1317","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","1308–1378":"1308–1378","1318–1358":"1318–1358","–1339":"–1339","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1267–Female":"1267–Kuollut","19 Jul 1329":"19. heinäkuuta 1329","20 Apr 1344":"20. huhtikuuta 1344","1285":"1285","1280":"1280","1358":"1358","1215":"1215","1303":"1303","1378":"1378","1267":"1267","1344":"1344","1265":"1265","1308":"1308","1318":"1318","1329":"1329","1317":"1317","1339":"1339","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Irlanti","County Kerry, Ireland":"County Kerry, Irlanti","Battle of Thurles (Slain)":"Battle, Camrose Co